# Adding a New Amulet ‚Äî Stacking-First Design

Every amulet **MUST** be designed so that N copies equipped at once still work. The universal rule:

> **Each equipped amulet operates independently. Visible effects naturally aggregate.**

There is no "no-stack" amulet. Even amulets with seemingly-binary effects (e.g. `ÂèåÂÆàÊä§Âú£Áõæ`) must scale with N ‚Äî otherwise duplicates are dead loot.

## 1. Pick the stacking category

Before writing any code, decide which category your amulet falls into:

| Category | Aggregation field shape | Consumer formula | Examples |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Linear (√óN)** | `xCount: number` (++) | magnitude √ó N | `dual-guard`, `strength`, `balance`, `stun-rate-boost` (+20N), `stun-gold` (+10N) |
| **Compound (2^N)** | `xCount: number` (++) | `Math.pow(2, count)` | `heal` (√ó2^N), `flash` (attack / 2^N) |
| **Summed bonus** | `xCount: number` + `xBonus: number` (per-amulet bonus summed) | use `xBonus` directly | `persuade-on-temp-attack` (10/20 per amulet), `persuade-grant-recycle-fetch` (1/2 per amulet via `‚Ä¶Total`) |
| **Progress counter** | `xCount: number` (++) | streak/progress `+= count` per qualifying event | `damage-class-discover`, `magic-class-discover`, `monster-kill-upgrade`, `flip-overkill-lifesteal`, `recycle-backpack-expand`, `equip-amulet-cap`, `stun-attempt-discover`, `swap-upgrade` |
| **Discrete event √óN** | `xCount: number` (++) | fire `count` independent triggers (or magnitude √ó N) | `discard-zap`, `flip-zap`, `catapult` (2N draws), `flip-gold` (5N gold), `card-gain-missile`, `dungeon-gold`, `monster-equip-buff` |
| **Independent √óN** | `xCount: number` (++) | each amulet's effect applied independently | `recycle-forge`, `equipment-salvage`, `lone-card` |

If the new amulet doesn't fit one of these ‚Äî **stop and ask** the user before inventing a new stacking shape.

## 2. Required wiring

### a. Add the typed effect id

`AmuletEffectId` union in [`GameCard.tsx`](client/src/components/GameCard.tsx). Use `kebab-case`.

### b. Add the aggregation field

[`ActiveAmuletEffects`](client/src/components/game-board/types.ts) ‚Äî pick a shape from the table above.
Add a JSDoc comment explaining the stacking convention if it's non-obvious (compound / summed bonus).

### c. Initialize in the empty factory

[`createEmptyAmuletEffects`](client/src/game-core/constants.ts) ‚Äî counters ‚Üí `0`, sums ‚Üí `0`.

### d. Aggregate in the canonical switch

[`computeAmuletEffects`](client/src/game-core/equipment.ts) ‚Äî `case 'my-effect': effects.myCount += 1; break;` (or `+= bonus`). **Never** assign (`= 1` / `= bonus`); always accumulate.

```typescript
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî doesn't stack
case 'dual-guard': effects.hasDualGuard = true; break;
case 'life': effects.lifeOverkillBonus = 3; break;

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî stacks linearly
case 'dual-guard': effects.dualGuardCount += 1; break;
case 'life': effects.lifeOverkillBonus += 3; break;
```

### e. Consume by count, not by boolean

In rule files / hooks / components, gate on `count > 0` and **scale the magnitude by count**:

```typescript
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî single-amulet behavior
if (amuletFx.hasFlipGold) {
  patch.gold = (state.gold ?? 0) + FLIP_GOLD_REWARD;
}

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî N amulets ‚Üí N √ó reward
if (amuletFx.flipGoldCount > 0) {
  patch.gold = (state.gold ?? 0) + FLIP_GOLD_REWARD * amuletFx.flipGoldCount;
}
```

For **progress counters**, increment by `count`, not `+1`:

```typescript
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî 1 amulet vs 5 amulets behave the same
const amulet = state.amuletSlots.find(s => s?.amuletEffect === 'monster-kill-upgrade');
if (amulet) progress += 1;

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî N amulets fire threshold N√ó faster
const amulets = state.amuletSlots.filter(s => s?.amuletEffect === 'monster-kill-upgrade');
if (amulets.length > 0) progress += amulets.length;
```

For **discrete event triggers** that emit a side-effect for UI animation, pass `count` in the payload and have the consumer queue N animations:

```typescript
// reducer side
sideEffects.push({ event: 'card:flipShock', payload: { count: amuletFx.flipZapCount } });

// hook side
useGameEvent('card:flipShock', ({ count }) => {
  for (let i = 0; i < count; i++) queueZapFlight();
});
```

### f. Add a stacking test

In [`amulet-stacking.test.ts`](client/src/game-core/__tests__/amulet-stacking.test.ts), add a case under the matching category that asserts on the count/bonus produced by `computeAmuletEffects` for `[amulet, amulet]` (and where applicable, the consumer-side magnitude).

## 3. Forbidden patterns

- ‚ùå `effects.hasMyAmulet: boolean` ‚Äî booleans cannot stack
- ‚ùå `effects.myField = value` (assignment) inside the switch ‚Äî clobbers prior amulets
- ‚ùå `if (state.amuletSlots.some(s => s?.amuletEffect === 'x'))` in consumer code ‚Äî bypasses the count and treats N copies as 1
- ‚ùå `amuletSlots.find(...)` to advance a progress counter by `+1` ‚Äî must use `filter().length` and add `length`
- ‚ùå Designing an amulet whose duplicates are explicitly "no-op" ‚Äî all amulets must scale, even if subtly

